WEBVTT

00:02.462 --> 00:06.433
Andy got back from London two days ago
and he still has jet lag.

00:06.553 --> 00:07.820
It's really annoying.

00:07.854 --> 00:09.411
We're on totally different
schedules.

00:09.531 --> 00:12.091
Last night he mowed the lawn
at 2:00 in the morning.

00:12.211 --> 00:14.777
Andy!
Andy!

00:14.828 --> 00:16.879
- Get me a beer?
- All right.

00:16.913 --> 00:17.863
As soon as I wake up,

00:17.898 --> 00:19.896
he goes down.
Hard.

00:20.206 --> 00:21.867
This has to stop!

00:21.901 --> 00:23.869
- [Snores]
- Babe, wake up.

00:23.887 --> 00:26.689
That's my spaghetti, Chewbacca.

00:26.723 --> 00:27.656
Babe!

00:27.691 --> 00:29.546
[Clanging]

00:29.783 --> 00:32.301
You hungry, Champion?

00:32.336 --> 00:33.636
[Gasps] Oh, my God.

00:33.670 --> 00:35.104
Are you kidding me?

00:39.343 --> 00:41.944
Hey. Oh, man,
I fell asleep again.

00:41.979 --> 00:43.613
Andy, you have got to stay up

00:43.664 --> 00:45.047
and get on a regular schedule.

00:45.082 --> 00:48.351
Were you about to spray me
with the hose inside the house?

00:48.402 --> 00:51.170
- Yeah.
- I kinda want you to do it now.

00:51.204 --> 00:53.256
- Okay.
- Aah! Aah!

00:53.307 --> 00:54.724
- Aaahhh!
- [Shouting]

00:54.758 --> 00:57.693
No, no, no, no, no, no!

00:57.744 --> 00:59.629
[Screaming]

01:01.598 --> 01:04.500
[Triumphant music]

01:04.534 --> 01:12.408
â™ª

01:13.097 --> 01:20.141
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny</font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.addic7ed.com</font>

01:21.512 --> 01:24.136
Okay, just a reminder, guys,
today is Leslie's last day

01:24.154 --> 01:25.655
as a city councilor,

01:25.706 --> 01:27.757
so everyone be extra supportive.

01:27.791 --> 01:28.758
Already done.

01:28.809 --> 01:30.593
When she walked past me
this morning,

01:30.644 --> 01:33.145
I gave her a kind nod.

01:33.163 --> 01:34.547
Heartwarming.

01:34.581 --> 01:36.182
Also I want to get her
a present to cheer her up

01:36.216 --> 01:37.316
on her last day.

01:37.351 --> 01:38.818
Any ideas?

01:38.852 --> 01:40.569
A "sorry you lost
your dream job" gift?

01:40.621 --> 01:42.555
Mm, that's a tough one.
Stay away from wine.

01:42.589 --> 01:43.823
Wine is crying juice.

01:43.857 --> 01:45.441
Well, I mean, you know her
better than anybody.

01:45.492 --> 01:48.210
What does she really want?
More than anything in the world?

01:48.261 --> 01:50.913
A nice candle.
I'm screwed.

01:50.947 --> 01:53.098
- [Gasps]
- No! Andy!

01:53.116 --> 01:54.867
- An-Andy!
- Oh! Come on!

01:54.901 --> 01:57.303
- Andy!
- Be right out.

01:57.337 --> 02:00.339
Well, this is the
Pawnee City Council chambers.

02:00.357 --> 02:02.425
Your new home away from me.

02:02.459 --> 02:04.427
Well, technically, my home
away from home is in Zurich.

02:04.461 --> 02:07.530
Frank Gehry designed it.
But this is nice too.

02:07.564 --> 02:08.614
Today is my last day

02:08.649 --> 02:10.616
[hoarsely]
As a--excuse me.

02:10.633 --> 02:12.385
[Clears throat]
Let me try this again.

02:12.419 --> 02:13.869
Today is [Hoarsely]
my last day at C--

02:13.904 --> 02:15.688
[full voice]
Today is my la--

02:15.722 --> 02:16.789
[high pitched]
Today is my last d--

02:16.823 --> 02:18.107
You know what?
You get the idea.

02:18.141 --> 02:20.142
My old friend Ingrid de Forest
won the recall vote,

02:20.193 --> 02:22.211
and she's taking my place
on Monday morning.

02:22.245 --> 02:23.579
But, you know, luckily for me,

02:23.630 --> 02:24.880
I've processed all my feelings.

02:24.931 --> 02:27.350
And I've gone through
the five stages of grief:

02:27.401 --> 02:29.368
Denial, anger,
Internet commenting,

02:29.403 --> 02:30.803
cat adoption, African dance,

02:30.837 --> 02:33.055
cat returning
to the adoption place,

02:33.106 --> 02:34.707
watching all the episodes
of <i>Murphy Brown,</i>

02:34.741 --> 02:36.359
and not giving a flying fart.

02:36.393 --> 02:38.461
How many stages is that?

02:38.512 --> 02:39.462
I don't know.

02:39.496 --> 02:41.197
The point is I'm fine now.

02:41.231 --> 02:43.199
This must be hard for you.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.518
It's like what
sir Ian McKellen said to me

02:45.552 --> 02:47.470
the day I sold my boat
to Karl Lagerfeld:

02:47.521 --> 02:49.905
"Parting is such sweet sorrow."

02:49.956 --> 02:52.208
Oh, my God.
What is your life?

02:52.259 --> 02:53.419
If it makes any difference,

02:53.427 --> 02:55.461
your work here
was a real inspiration to me,

02:55.495 --> 02:58.881
and I am going to do my best
to continue your legacy.

02:58.932 --> 03:02.068
Well, I appreciate
the sentiment.

03:02.102 --> 03:05.237
[Exhales]

03:05.255 --> 03:06.889
- Leslie.
- [Gasps]

03:06.923 --> 03:08.574
I'm sorry.
Was I singing

03:08.608 --> 03:10.476
<i>Goodbye Yellow Brick Road</i>
out loud?

03:10.510 --> 03:12.745
No. But would you like to?

03:12.779 --> 03:14.113
I studied opera at the Sorbonne.

03:14.147 --> 03:15.464
I'd be happy to harmonize.

03:15.515 --> 03:17.266
[Sings] Goodbye...

03:17.317 --> 03:18.984
[Sings operatically]
Goodbye...

03:19.018 --> 03:20.369
Naw.

03:20.404 --> 03:21.954
And finally,

03:21.988 --> 03:23.839
here is a check
for the entirety

03:23.890 --> 03:25.241
of the purchase
of Rent-A-Swag.

03:25.275 --> 03:27.392
And here is a personal note

03:27.411 --> 03:29.495
from my client
Dr. Saperstein.

03:29.529 --> 03:30.713
"Dear Tom:
I win.

03:30.747 --> 03:32.415
"You suck.
Turn note over.

03:32.466 --> 03:33.465
"You still suck.

03:33.483 --> 03:35.284
Turn note over."

03:35.318 --> 03:37.369
Okay, Saperstein
couldn't even face me himself?

03:37.403 --> 03:38.504
He had to send in his lackey?

03:38.538 --> 03:39.505
My client isn't at this meeting

03:39.539 --> 03:40.923
because he doesn't have to be.

03:40.974 --> 03:42.174
Successful people,
Mr. Haverford,

03:42.209 --> 03:44.810
use their money to use others
to work for them.

03:44.828 --> 03:46.829
Hmm, it's an interesting idea,
lawyer-dude.

03:46.880 --> 03:48.731
What if I gave you 5 bucks
to put a bag of poop

03:48.765 --> 03:49.765
in Saperstein's car?

03:49.816 --> 03:51.033
No.
[Locks click]

03:51.067 --> 03:53.753
Ballpark me.
How much would it cost?

03:53.787 --> 03:54.754
$10,000.

03:54.788 --> 03:56.422
Counter-offer:

03:56.456 --> 03:57.807
Why don't you just do it
for the story?

03:57.841 --> 04:00.392
Goodbye, Mr. Haverford.

04:00.410 --> 04:01.877
Is it done?

04:01.912 --> 04:05.231
Well, how many times
did he turn the paper over?

04:05.265 --> 04:08.701
Oh, that is disappointing.

04:08.735 --> 04:09.610
So...

04:09.730 --> 04:10.520
look at this baby.

04:10.640 --> 04:12.671
That is
the most symmetrical fetus

04:12.705 --> 04:13.689
I've ever seen.

04:13.723 --> 04:15.808
This could be a superhero.

04:15.826 --> 04:17.243
- Dr. Saperstein.
- Yes.

04:17.277 --> 04:18.711
I know that we should hate you

04:18.745 --> 04:20.329
because you destroyed
our friend's business.

04:20.363 --> 04:22.381
- But we love you so much!
- We love you!

04:22.399 --> 04:23.549
I'm loveable!

04:23.567 --> 04:25.317
So do you wanna know the sex?

04:25.335 --> 04:27.136
Oh, my God.
Should we?

04:27.170 --> 04:29.254
N-no, right?
Or maybe yes?

04:29.272 --> 04:31.157
Is there an option
other than yes or no?

04:31.191 --> 04:32.291
I'll tell you
what I'm gonna do.

04:32.325 --> 04:33.709
I'm gonna write it down.

04:33.743 --> 04:35.427
Then I'm gonna put it
in an envelope,

04:35.462 --> 04:36.512
seal it, and when you're ready,

04:36.563 --> 04:37.847
voila!

04:37.898 --> 04:40.449
- That'll be fun!
- That's like the Oscars.

04:40.484 --> 04:42.334
[Laughs]
Hey, let's get some food.

04:42.368 --> 04:43.586
I'm starving.

04:43.637 --> 04:45.104
Wait, no, I have to pee.

04:45.138 --> 04:46.522
Wait, no, I have to barf.

04:46.556 --> 04:48.307
Actually, all three.

04:48.325 --> 04:50.509
Being pregnant is great.

04:50.544 --> 04:53.462
And, finally, Larry's share
of the profit.

04:53.513 --> 04:54.730
Whoa! Good to be Larry.

04:54.764 --> 04:55.815
No, it's not,
you boring grandpa.

04:55.849 --> 04:58.617
Meanwhile, Tommy's ridin' high.

04:58.635 --> 04:59.751
$32,000.

04:59.769 --> 05:00.919
I'm basically a millionaire.

05:00.937 --> 05:02.154
What are you gonna do
with the money, Tom?

05:02.189 --> 05:03.405
Glad you asked.

05:03.440 --> 05:05.457
A horrible man recently gave me
some great advice.

05:05.492 --> 05:07.893
For years, I've been coming up
with my own ideas.

05:07.928 --> 05:10.129
Like some sort of
non-rich idiot.

05:10.163 --> 05:12.097
Now I'm gonna let people
come to me

05:12.115 --> 05:13.866
and invest my scrilla
in the best idea I hear.

05:13.900 --> 05:14.867
That sounds like

05:14.885 --> 05:16.552
an efficient use
of the free market.

05:16.586 --> 05:18.320
I would wish you
the best of luck,

05:18.355 --> 05:21.156
but I believe luck is
a concept invented by the weak

05:21.208 --> 05:22.591
to explain their failures.

05:22.626 --> 05:24.209
Come hear the ideas
with me, Ron.

05:24.227 --> 05:25.728
I could use your wise,
grandfatherly advice.

05:25.779 --> 05:28.280
Do you think everyone here
is a grandfather?

05:28.314 --> 05:29.281
Basically, if you're
older than me,

05:29.299 --> 05:30.449
you're a grandpa.

05:30.467 --> 05:31.783
And if you are a grandpa,
you're dead.

05:31.801 --> 05:32.751
That sounds right.

05:32.769 --> 05:33.769
Uh, oops.

05:33.820 --> 05:35.141
This check is made out
to "Lenny,"

05:35.155 --> 05:36.906
which I think is a typo
for "Larry,"

05:36.957 --> 05:38.541
which isn't
even actually my name.

05:38.575 --> 05:40.676
[Laughs] Well, tell it
to the bank, Lenny.

05:40.727 --> 05:43.095
Am I--am I Lenny now?

05:43.129 --> 05:46.065
I'd like to order
a singing telegram.

05:46.099 --> 05:49.251
Well, my wife lost her job,
so maybe something sad and slow.

05:49.286 --> 05:50.352
Do you know anything from

05:50.387 --> 05:51.937
<i>The Requiem for a Dream</i>
soundtrack?

05:51.972 --> 05:53.155
This is a bad idea.

05:53.189 --> 05:54.557
I'm hanging up now. Bye.

05:54.608 --> 05:56.441
Well, Ingrid is settled
into my office,

05:56.459 --> 05:58.460
and this box contains
the last of my stuff.

05:58.511 --> 06:00.462
Although I might have left
some salt packets in my desk.

06:00.513 --> 06:02.047
Maybe I should go back
for those?

06:02.081 --> 06:03.816
Honey, it's okay,
there'll be other salt packets.

06:03.850 --> 06:05.734
But not the kind
that snaps in half, maybe.

06:05.785 --> 06:07.670
Okay, I know
I'm a broken record,

06:07.704 --> 06:09.788
but getting away
from the City Council

06:09.822 --> 06:11.262
is absolutely
the best thing for you.

06:11.291 --> 06:13.559
Trust me.

06:13.593 --> 06:15.861
This is Perd Hapley
talking to you now

06:15.896 --> 06:18.230
about what's going on today.

06:18.248 --> 06:19.832
We're live at City Hall

06:19.866 --> 06:21.967
where City Councilman Dexhart
is addressing

06:22.001 --> 06:23.319
his latest sex scandal.

06:23.353 --> 06:26.188
Recently, certain allegations
have come to light

06:26.222 --> 06:28.457
about my inappropriate conduct.

06:28.491 --> 06:31.477
I'm here
to set the record straight.

06:31.511 --> 06:35.147
I totally did all of it.

06:35.181 --> 06:37.366
Another sex scandal?
This guy's unbelievable.

06:37.417 --> 06:38.751
How does he find the time?

06:38.785 --> 06:41.420
I also engaged in
inappropriate texting,

06:41.454 --> 06:44.673
sexting,
and tex-mexting,

06:44.708 --> 06:47.326
which is where you send
photos of your junk

06:47.360 --> 06:49.778
from the restroom
of a chili's to go.

06:49.813 --> 06:51.630
- Hmm.
- Ew.

06:51.648 --> 06:53.465
Does this make me a bad boy?

06:53.500 --> 06:55.234
You tell me.

06:55.268 --> 06:56.485
No. Really.

06:56.519 --> 06:57.536
Tell me.

06:57.570 --> 06:59.905
It gets me off
when women tell me that.

06:59.923 --> 07:01.423
He's reading this,
he wrote this down.

07:01.458 --> 07:04.443
I sent these texts
to roughly 100 women

07:04.477 --> 07:06.545
under the following pseudonyms:
[Clears throat]

07:06.563 --> 07:07.879
Enrique Shockwave,

07:07.897 --> 07:10.115
Willie Dynamite,

07:10.150 --> 07:12.518
Lee Harvey Teabag...

07:12.552 --> 07:13.719
Well, at least
you won't have to deal

07:13.737 --> 07:15.104
with that guy anymore.

07:15.155 --> 07:17.055
- You're right.
- Lieutenant Wilhelm Von Penis.

07:17.073 --> 07:19.224
Not after someone beats him
in the next election.

07:19.242 --> 07:21.610
Someone who is smart
and hard-working

07:21.661 --> 07:24.029
and who knows the job
because she's done it already

07:24.063 --> 07:26.165
and is also blond
and named Leslie

07:26.199 --> 07:27.166
and loves you.

07:27.200 --> 07:29.668
- Is it you?
- Yes! It is!

07:29.703 --> 07:30.836
I'm gonna run again.

07:30.870 --> 07:32.338
I'm gonna beat Dexhart!

07:32.372 --> 07:33.505
And Anthony Weiner.

07:34.533 --> 07:36.804
Another City Council campaign?

07:36.924 --> 07:38.238
Leslie, think about what you're saying.

07:38.358 --> 07:40.446
I did. I challenge you
to find one flaw in my plan.

07:40.497 --> 07:41.747
Well, for one,

07:41.798 --> 07:43.065
we don't even live
in Dexhart's district.

07:43.100 --> 07:44.183
Not yet!

07:44.542 --> 07:46.426
But we can go and rent
a second apartment,

07:46.477 --> 07:48.345
and we can spend 51%
of our time there.

07:48.379 --> 07:49.696
And then I'll file
the campaign form

07:49.731 --> 07:51.131
from that address.

07:51.165 --> 07:53.717
I don't want to spend 51%
of our time in his district.

07:53.751 --> 07:55.902
It's basically a dumping ground
for old shipping containers.

07:55.937 --> 07:58.154
It's like a raccoon shantytown.

07:58.172 --> 07:59.373
Oh, it's not that bad.

07:59.424 --> 08:01.341
And also, Dexhart fights dirty.

08:01.392 --> 08:02.559
He's never lost an election

08:02.577 --> 08:05.379
because he runs brutal,
scorched-earth campaigns.

08:05.413 --> 08:06.880
So what? I got plenty
of dirt on that scumbag.

08:06.914 --> 08:08.098
I say, "Bring it on."

08:08.132 --> 08:09.449
So I'm gonna start

08:09.484 --> 08:11.001
my negative PR blitz
against Dexhart and--

08:11.035 --> 08:14.638
Look, I just think we need
to take a deep breath...

08:14.656 --> 08:16.273
Think about
if this is really worth it.

08:16.307 --> 08:20.010
Anything is worth me
getting back on City Council.

08:20.044 --> 08:21.612
Okay.
[Claps once]

08:21.646 --> 08:23.530
Let's see which one
of these lucky visionaries

08:23.564 --> 08:25.532
is gonna make me rich.

08:25.583 --> 08:27.718
Greg Phillips!

08:27.752 --> 08:29.303
Hi, guys, thanks
for meeting with me.

08:29.354 --> 08:30.404
Enough chitchat. What's
your pitch, kid?

08:30.438 --> 08:31.855
Come on, time is money,
money is power,

08:31.889 --> 08:33.307
power is pizza,
pizza is knowledge.

08:33.341 --> 08:34.508
- Let's go.
- Okay.

08:34.558 --> 08:38.996
So my idea is for an abacus,
but on your phone.

08:39.030 --> 08:41.530
I call it a "phone-bacus."

08:41.566 --> 08:44.634
Son, you just described
a calculator.

08:44.652 --> 08:46.770
Hey, but you're talking
about it, right?

08:46.804 --> 08:47.838
Three words:

08:47.872 --> 08:50.207
Automated word counter.

08:50.241 --> 08:51.641
Get out.

08:51.659 --> 08:53.109
[Robotic voice]
Two. Words.

08:53.127 --> 08:55.345
- No.
- One. Word.

08:55.380 --> 08:57.014
As you may know,

08:57.048 --> 08:59.533
I do like to tinker with things
in my garage.

08:59.584 --> 09:01.818
I'm gonna hit the can
while he's up.

09:01.836 --> 09:03.136
So I think I have discovered

09:03.171 --> 09:07.541
a way to generate
clean, renewable energy.

09:07.575 --> 09:09.309
I think it's gonna ch--

09:09.344 --> 09:10.394
[sneezes]

09:10.428 --> 09:11.461
Oh! Gross!

09:11.479 --> 09:12.646
God, Larry.

09:12.697 --> 09:13.730
You sneezed all over us!

09:13.764 --> 09:14.831
I'm not gonna buy that thing.

09:14.865 --> 09:16.466
It's covered in a gallon
of your boogers.

09:16.467 --> 09:18.301
I totally understand.

09:19.354 --> 09:22.205
[Sneezes]

09:22.240 --> 09:23.790
Uh, jeez.

09:23.841 --> 09:26.576
I will be thrilled
if we have a girl.

09:26.611 --> 09:28.195
Oh, tiny dresses?

09:28.246 --> 09:29.612
Braids?
Glitter on everything?

09:29.630 --> 09:30.630
Forget it.

09:30.665 --> 09:32.399
And also, girls' names
are so cute.

09:32.450 --> 09:34.901
Daisy, Annabelle, Lilly.

09:34.952 --> 09:38.939
Olive, rosemary, chicken.
Fifty burritos.

09:38.973 --> 09:40.557
Oh, my God, I'm starving.
Miss, hi!

09:40.575 --> 09:42.626
I'm pregnant, and I'm
a little bit crazy.

09:42.660 --> 09:43.710
So if you don't bring
our appetizers out

09:43.761 --> 09:44.995
in the next 30 seconds,

09:45.029 --> 09:48.398
I'm gonna plunge your face
into the deep fryer!

09:48.416 --> 09:49.383
And also two waters, please.

09:49.417 --> 09:51.034
But no hurry.

09:51.052 --> 09:52.319
Thank you.

09:52.353 --> 09:53.437
Leslie, I don't know
if there's a story

09:53.471 --> 09:54.637
in these emails.

09:54.655 --> 09:56.089
They're iffy,

09:56.124 --> 09:57.707
but Dexhart
has been elected eight times.

09:57.725 --> 09:59.593
I don't think the voters care.

09:59.644 --> 10:01.678
His poll numbers are actually up
since the scandal broke.

10:01.696 --> 10:02.812
Well, that's
just because people found out

10:02.830 --> 10:04.364
he was Miley Cyrus' cousin.

10:04.415 --> 10:05.882
- He is?
- Good morning, Leslie.

10:05.916 --> 10:07.934
"Sweet jugs."

10:10.071 --> 10:11.187
What?

10:11.205 --> 10:12.572
He's kinda cute.

10:12.607 --> 10:14.007
Oh, God, Shauna, no.

10:14.058 --> 10:16.309
I-I just feel like
I could fix him, you know?

10:16.360 --> 10:17.577
[Puffs]

10:17.612 --> 10:19.229
This sucks!

10:19.263 --> 10:21.498
We heard a hundred pitches,
and they're all terrible.

10:21.516 --> 10:23.150
Change of plans.

10:23.184 --> 10:24.151
You guys are my idea factory.

10:24.202 --> 10:25.836
- April, go.
- Okay, got one.

10:25.870 --> 10:27.737
Macaroni and poison.

10:27.755 --> 10:30.173
It's like mac and cheese,
but with a special ingredient.

10:30.207 --> 10:31.174
Ron?

10:31.192 --> 10:32.609
Every socket set
I've ever bought

10:32.643 --> 10:34.494
only goes up to 1/2 inch.

10:34.545 --> 10:36.413
I'd love a couple larger sizes.

10:36.447 --> 10:38.848
Take it all the way up to 5/8.

10:38.866 --> 10:39.866
Andy?

10:39.917 --> 10:43.970
Bears bouncing
on trampoline roads.

10:44.021 --> 10:46.823
There's a chance
that I might have dreamed that.

10:46.858 --> 10:49.126
Okay, time to head back
to the office.

10:49.160 --> 10:51.011
I've missed
an entire day of work,

10:51.045 --> 10:54.614
so at least some good
came from this.

10:54.649 --> 10:56.065
What are you doing?

10:56.083 --> 10:57.868
Well, they couldn't make
a banner in time

10:57.902 --> 11:00.570
