with the TV,

15:00.085 --> 15:01.535
where it keeps ordering porno,

15:01.569 --> 15:02.903
like, a ton of porno.

15:02.938 --> 15:05.258
Like, how can someone watch
that much porno in one sitting?

15:05.273 --> 15:06.594
Only when you're out
of the house.

15:06.625 --> 15:08.976
So if you see it on the bill,
that's why. Okay?

15:09.027 --> 15:11.261
"And therefore, with your help,

15:11.279 --> 15:13.497
"we can make our future bright.

15:13.531 --> 15:16.934
I believe I still have
a lot to offer this city."

15:16.968 --> 15:18.802
I'd swap those two lines.

15:18.820 --> 15:22.473
Always helps
to end on the call to action.

15:22.507 --> 15:24.391
I'm sorry if it felt like
everyone piled on.

15:24.442 --> 15:26.193
We were just being honest.

15:26.227 --> 15:27.678
But if you really
want to do this,

15:27.712 --> 15:29.096
of course we'll support you.

15:29.130 --> 15:30.431
Thank you.

15:30.482 --> 15:32.449
I'm sorry I stormed out.

15:32.483 --> 15:33.867
You know, I've been thinking
for weeks of what to get you

15:33.918 --> 15:35.970
as a "last day in City Council"
present.

15:36.021 --> 15:38.322
And I finally figured it out.

15:38.356 --> 15:39.406
You remember Jen Barkley,

15:39.457 --> 15:40.741
political consultant
and power broker?

15:40.792 --> 15:42.042
Hey! Jen!

15:42.093 --> 15:43.093
What brings you back to Pawnee?

15:43.128 --> 15:44.511
Ben bought one hour of my time.

15:44.562 --> 15:45.929
I heard you need
some consulting?

15:45.947 --> 15:47.965
Well, uh, I guess.

15:47.999 --> 15:49.583
I mean, how are you?
How's your family?

15:49.634 --> 15:51.518
Okay, I get paid
$1,200 an hour.

15:51.569 --> 15:53.337
Do you really wanna spend
any of that time

15:53.371 --> 15:54.404
talking about my mother

15:54.422 --> 15:56.557
and her
19-year-old Korean husband?

15:56.608 --> 15:58.008
Well, that does sound
fascinating.

15:58.009 --> 15:59.026
But you're right, let's talk.

15:59.060 --> 16:01.445
Okay.
I'll get the chair. [Laughs]

16:03.131 --> 16:05.065
[Prolonged] Ron!

16:05.100 --> 16:06.734
That's how I enter rooms now.
It's more dramatic.

16:06.785 --> 16:08.786
Why did you enter at all?

16:08.820 --> 16:10.187
Because I have some huge news.

16:10.221 --> 16:14.708
You're looking at
Pawnee's new business liaison.

16:14.743 --> 16:15.993
I don't like French words.

16:16.027 --> 16:17.328
I do like the word "business."

16:17.362 --> 16:18.612
You may continue.

16:18.646 --> 16:20.080
April created
a new position for herself,

16:20.115 --> 16:21.281
and I wanna do the same.

16:21.333 --> 16:22.833
The town could use
more private-sector money

16:22.867 --> 16:23.851
after the merger.

16:23.902 --> 16:25.135
So as business liaison,

16:25.153 --> 16:27.354
I would find companies
looking to move or expand,

16:27.389 --> 16:29.123
and convince them
to do it in Pawnee.

16:29.174 --> 16:31.041
Now this is a good idea.

16:31.059 --> 16:33.177
You've come a long way, son.

16:33.211 --> 16:35.612
And while I got you here...

16:35.646 --> 16:36.597
talking tissue.

16:36.631 --> 16:38.599
Go for it.

16:38.650 --> 16:39.650
[Tom's voice] Yo, dog!

16:39.684 --> 16:41.835
Life is what you make of it.

16:41.870 --> 16:45.339
Leave while I'm ahead?
You got it.

16:46.691 --> 16:48.025
Clear them sinuses, playboy!

16:48.059 --> 16:49.493
Someone's got the sniffies.

16:49.527 --> 16:50.744
Tell your mama you love 'er.

16:50.795 --> 16:52.496
Step up
your vitamin "C" game, bro!

16:52.530 --> 16:54.314
So they recall me
after all I've done for them.

16:54.349 --> 16:55.432
Ridiculous.

16:55.450 --> 16:56.583
But Dexhart now
has another sex scandal.

16:56.618 --> 16:57.901
Of course he does.

16:57.936 --> 16:59.720
And the plan is
I'm gonna run for his seat.

16:59.754 --> 17:02.072
Because how do I lose
to a guy like that?

17:02.107 --> 17:03.824
- That's a great idea, right?
- It's a terrible idea.

17:03.875 --> 17:05.659
I knew it. Wait. What?

17:05.710 --> 17:07.094
First of all, you <i>could</i> lose
to a guy like that.

17:07.127 --> 17:09.346
Terrible people defeat
great people all of the time.

17:09.380 --> 17:10.614
I should know.

17:10.647 --> 17:11.865
Those terrible people
have paid me so much money,

17:11.900 --> 17:13.384
I have a condo
in every virgin island.

17:13.417 --> 17:14.968
Now you might win.

17:15.002 --> 17:17.104
You're smart, Ben is smart,
you might win.

17:17.137 --> 17:18.571
But why would you want to?

17:18.606 --> 17:20.523
Because it's my dream job.

17:20.541 --> 17:21.825
Then dream bigger.

17:21.843 --> 17:23.794
Look, you love this town.

17:23.828 --> 17:24.895
It's being run
by monsters and morons?

17:24.929 --> 17:26.180
Get a better job!

17:26.231 --> 17:27.781
Rise above their heads.

17:27.816 --> 17:29.900
Affect change at a higher level.

17:29.918 --> 17:30.968
Don't be the kid
that graduates high school,

17:31.002 --> 17:32.586
hangs out
in the school parking lot.

17:32.637 --> 17:34.388
Be the woman who moves away,

17:34.439 --> 17:36.607
climbs the ladder,
and then confidently comes back

17:36.641 --> 17:38.008
and has sex
with her hot old English teacher

17:38.042 --> 17:39.443
just for kicks.

17:39.461 --> 17:40.961
Is that what you did?

17:41.012 --> 17:42.012
Yeah. Mr. Baker.

17:42.046 --> 17:43.597
Sex was pretty good,
thanks to me.

17:43.648 --> 17:45.983
Look, Pawnee
has done you a favor.

17:46.017 --> 17:47.451
You've outgrown them.

17:47.485 --> 17:49.786
You've got talent, and
you've got name recognition.

17:49.804 --> 17:52.272
Which means that you have
a bright, wide-open future

17:52.323 --> 17:54.408
with a thousand options.

17:54.442 --> 17:56.026
State Senate.

17:56.060 --> 17:57.194
Federal jobs.

17:57.228 --> 17:58.796
Even congress.

17:58.830 --> 18:01.432
All of these are doable for you.

18:01.466 --> 18:04.301
And you can trust me...

18:05.904 --> 18:09.189
because I don't care
enough about you to lie.

18:09.240 --> 18:10.991
